ction is extortionate, \par }}\pard\plain\nosnaplinegrid\b0\i0\fs22\qj\sb0\sa80\li1200\sl260{{\b0\i0\nosupersub\nosupersub\fs22\qj\qj\li1200\cf1 \f0 the court may reopen the transaction so as to do justice between the parties having regard to all the circumstances, and, for that purpose, make such orders and give such directions in respect of the terms of the transaction or the rights of the parties thereunder as the court may think fit. \par }}\pard\plain\nosnaplinegrid\b0\i0\fs22\qj\sb0\sa80\fi-1080\li1200\tqr\tx960\sl260{\tab{\b0\i0\nosupersub\nosupersub\fs22\qj\qj\li1200\cf1 \f0 (2)}{\b0\i0\nosupersub\nosupersub\fs22\qj\qj\li1200\cf1 \f0 \tab }{\b0\i0\nosupersub\nosupersub\fs22\qj\qj\li1200\cf1 \f0 For the purposes of this section, a transaction is extortionate if\u8212??\par }}\pard\plain\nosnaplinegrid\b0\i0\fs22\qj\sb0\sa80\fi-1080\li1680\tqr\tx1440\sl260{\tab{\b0\i0\nosupersub\nosupersub\fs22\qj\qj\li1680\cf1 \f0 (a)}{\b0\i0\nosupersub\nosupersub\fs22\qj\qj\li1680\cf1 \f0 \tab }{\b0\i0\nosupersub\nosupersub\fs22\qj\qj\li1680\cf1 \f0 it requires the debtor or a relative of his to make payments (whether unconditionally or on certain contingencies) which are grossly exorbitant; or \par }}\pard\plain\nosnaplinegrid\b0\i0\fs22\qj\sb0\sa80\fi-1080\li1680\tqr\tx1440\sl260{\tab{\b0\i0\nosupersub\nosupersub\fs22\qj\qj\li1680\cf1 \f0 (b)}{\b0\i0\nosupersub\nosupersub\fs22\qj\qj\li1680\cf1 \f0 \tab }{\b0\i0\nosupersub\nosupersub\fs22\qj\qj\li1680\cf1 \f0 it otherwise grossly contravenes ordinary principles of fair-dealing. \par }}\pard\plain\nosnaplinegrid\b0\i0\fs22\qj\sb0\sa80\fi-1080\li1200\tqr\tx960\sl260{\tab{\b0\i0\nosupersub\nosupersub\fs22\qj\qj\li1200\cf1 \f0 (3)}{\b0\i0\nosupersub\nosupersub\fs22\qj\qj\li1200\cf1 \f0 \tab }{\b0\i0\nosupersub\nosupersub\fs22\qj\qj\li1200\cf1 \f0 Any agreement for the repayment of a loan or for the payment of interest on a loan in respect of which the effective rate of interest exceeds 36 per cent per annum shall, having regard to that fact alone, be presumed for the purposes of this section to be a transaction which is extortionate; but except where such rate exceeds the rate specified in }{\b0\i0\nosupersub\nosupersub\fs22\qj\qj\li1200\cf1 \f0 section 24(1)}{\b0\i0\nosupersub\nosupersub\fs22\qj\qj\li1200\cf1 \f0 , the court may declare that any such agreement is not extortionate for the purposes of this section if, having regard to all the circumstances relating to the agreement, the court is satisfied that such rate is not unreasonable or unfair. }{\b0\i\nosupersub\nosupersub\fs22\qj\qj\li1200\cf1 \f0 (Amended }{\b0\i\nosupersub\nosupersub\fs22\qj\qj\li1200\cf1 \f0 L.N. 208 of 2022}{\b0\i\nosupersub\nosupersub\fs22\qj\qj\li1200\cf1 \f0 )\par }}\pard\plain\nosnaplinegrid\b0\i0\fs22\qj\sb0\sa80\fi-1080\li1200\tqr\tx960\sl260{\tab{\b0\i0\nosupersub\nosupersub\fs22\qj\qj\li1200\cf1 \f0 (4)}{\b0\i0\nosupersub\nosupersub\fs22\qj\qj\li1200\cf1 \f0 \tab }{\b0\i0\nosupersub\nosupersub\fs22\qj\qj\li1200\cf1 \f0 In determining whether a transaction is extortionate for the purposes of this section, regard shall be had to such evidence as is adduced concerning\u8212??\par }}\pard\plain\nosnaplinegrid\b0\i0\fs22\qj\sb0\sa80\fi-1080\li1680\tqr\tx1440\sl260{\tab{\b0\i0\nosupersub\nosupersub\fs22\qj\qj\li1680\cf1 \f0 (a)}{\b0\i0\nosupersub\nosupersub\fs22\qj\qj\li1680\cf1 \f0 \tab }{\b0\i0\nosupersub\nosupersub\fs22\qj\qj\li1680\cf1 \f0 interest rate prevailing at the time it was made; \par }}\pard\plain\nosnaplinegrid\b0\i0\fs22\qj\sb0\sa80\fi-1080\li1680\tqr\tx1440\sl260{\tab{\b0\i0\nosupersub\nosupersub\fs22\qj\qj\li1680\cf1 \f0 (b)}{\b0\i0\nosupersub\nosupersub\fs22\qj\qj\li1680\cf1 \f0 \tab }{\b0\i0\nosupersub\nosupersub\fs22\qj\qj\li1680\cf1 \f0 the factors mentioned in subsections (5) and (6); and \par }}\pard\plain\nosnaplinegrid\b0\i0\fs22\qj\sb0\sa80\fi-1080\li1680\tqr\tx1440\sl260{\tab{\b0\i0\nosupersub\nosupersub\fs22\qj\qj\li1680\cf1 \f0 (c)}{\b0\i0\nosupersub\nosupersub\fs22\qj\qj\li1680\